            <GeneralInfo>
                <Name>RBBN</Name>
                <Name>Referentiebestand Belgisch-Nederlands</Name>
                <Name>Reference Lexicon for Belgian-Dutch</Name>
                <Version>1.0</Version>
                <Owner>Dutch Language Union (Nederlandse Taalunie; NTU)</Owner>
                <PublicationYear>2005</PublicationYear>
                <Description>
                    <Description>The Reference Lexicon for Belgian-Dutch is a monolingual lexicon of Belgian-Dutch, containing
                        ca. 4.000 entries (lemmas). The RBBN contains only those words which have a specific meaning in
                        Belgian-Dutch or appear only in Belgian-Dutch. If possible, the description is related to the
                        Northern Dutch variant, which is why the RBBN can be seen as a complement of the Reference
                        Lexicon for Dutch (RBN).
                    </Description>
                </Description>
            </GeneralInfo>
 
